<p class=indbig>
<b>OS/2</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>There&rsquo;s a place in this world for DOS and Windows.<br>
And you&rsquo;re looking at it.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
OS/2&reg; 2.0 isn&rsquo;t about leaving your DOS and Windows&trade; 
applications behind. It&rsquo;s about moving them ahead &ndash; doing 
more with them than ever before.
</p><p class=indbig>
Now you can run DOS, Windows and OS/2 applications at the same 
time, in separate windows on the same screen. Create a new letter 
while using your fax/modem. Print charts as you calculate a complex 
spreadsheet. Even &ldquo;cut and paste&rdquo; between any applications &ndash; 
and more. But OS/2 doesn&rsquo;t just enhance your current applications. 
It protects vour investment in them. And preserves your choices as 
more become available, including new 32-bit applications.
</p><p class=indbig>
But maybe the best part is that for less than the cost of DOS 
and Windows, you get the capabilities of both. Plus all the added benefits 
of OS/2 2.0 &ndash; including Adobe Type Manager.&trade; So with 
OS/2 2.0, whatever applications you use, you&rsquo;ve come to the 
right place. For an IBM authorized dealer near you, or to order 
OS/2 2.0 from IBM &ndash; at special introductory prices of $49 for 
Windows users and $99 from any DOS &ndash; call 
<b>1 800 3-IBM-OS2.<sup><small>*</small></sup></b>
</p><p class=indbig>
<b>Introducing OS/2 2.0.</b>
</p><p class=indbig>
